    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Region of the ozone layer in which the ozone concentration is substantially depleted, occurring chiefly at high latitudes and attributed to the chemical action of CFCs and other atmospheric pollutants.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>臭氧層中臭氧濃度受到大量損耗之區域，主要見於高緯度地區，氯氟碳化合物及其它大氣污染物產生化學作用為肇因。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Deel van de ozonlaag waarin de concentratie ozon min of meer is verdwenen. Dit gebeurt vooral op hoge geografische breedte en wordt voornamelijk toegeschreven aan de chemische werking van cfk's en andere atmosferische verontreinigingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
